<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="399" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperitum">Bembidion imperitum</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 91. Type locality: &quot;Victoria, Vancouver Island [British Columbia]&quot; (original citation for the lectotype). Lectotype (♂), designated by Lindroth (1975: 120), in USNM [# 36950]. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1963b: 357).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="399" pageNumber="400">
